track_notes: Park at the Mount Peeley Trailhead, which is at the end of a long dirt road (high clearance, preferably 4wd road).  The views are spectacular and the trail is decent.  It would be difficult to go up on the East side - too rocky and steep.  I went around to the North and found an easier way to bushwhack up.  The first part of the bushwhack is very steep but plenty of trees and the soil is soft enough.  This is a long hike so do not attempt it unless you are prepared.  I picked up Mount Peeley on the way back.
track_title: 7358 Peak and Mount Peeley via Arizona Trail
